Netflix in Nov.: Original series take over Here's what and when you can add to your queue next month: Post to Facebook Netflix in Nov.: Original series take over Here's what and when you can add to your queue next month:  //on.11alive.com/1LLyVJL   Join the Conversation To   Netflix in Nov.: Original series take over USA Today Network USA Today, news source 11:38 a.m. EDT October 21, 2015 No, Krysten Ritter has not fallen on hard times. The brown bag and scars on her face are for her title role in the new Netflix series "A.K.A. Jessica Jones." The show was filming in New York's Tribeca neighborhood on March 24. (Photo: Photo: Josiah Kamau, BuzzFoto via Getty Images) 
Come November, several Netflix originals are hitting the streaming service, from Marvel's Jessica Jones to Aziz Ansari's show Master of None and Bob Odenkirk and David Cross' sketch comedy series With Bob and David. 
Here's what and when you can add to your queue next month:
